https://github.com/libmbd/libmbd

follow the instructions in this page, but remember to use sudo privilege, because
the installation code(make -C build install) will try to copy the library to /usr/local/lib, 
which is a folder needs sudo to have access.



If you already installed libmbd and modified part of the source code and want to compile the code again.
just do this (usually I install libmbd without SCALAPACK_MPI so just ignore the text in bracket)
cmake -B build [-DENABLE_SCALAPACK_MPI=ON]
sudo make -C build install
